  <section id="Section605037">
    <title><anchor id="Anchor605036" role="Index"
    xreflabel="sales orders:list open " /> <indexterm significance="normal"
        zone="Anchor605036">
        <primary>sales orders</primary>

        <secondary>list open</secondary>
      </indexterm>List Open Sales Orders</title>

    <para id="Para605038">A Sales Order appears on the List Open Sales Orders
    screen if one or more of its Line Items remains open. Once all Line Items
    for a Sales Order have been closed, the Sales Order will no longer appear
    on the list. Typically, Sales Order Line Items are closed when the Order
    is selected for billing. To display open Sales Orders by Warehouse, select
    the "Open Sales Orders" option. The following screen will appear:</para>

    <para id="Para519185"><screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/SO_Ord_listOpenSO.png"
                       id="Graphic523353" />
          </imageobject>

          <caption id="Caption519186">Open Sales Orders Master List</caption>
        </mediaobject>
      </screenshot></para>

    <para id="Para519187">When displaying open Sales Orders, you are presented
    with the following options:</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry role="openmfg">
        <term id="Para519188">All Warehouses</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be1f8">
          <para>Select to display a list of open Sales Orders for all
          Warehouses.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry role="openmfg">
        <term id="Para519190">Selected</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be21c">
          <para>Specify Warehouse whose open Sales Orders you want to
          display.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para519192">Sales Orders</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be264">
          <para>Display lists open Sales Orders.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

    <para id="Para519194">To the far right of the screen, the following
    buttons are available:</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para519195">CLOSE</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be2d0">
          <para>Closes the screen, returning you to the application
          desktop.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para653631">PRINT</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be318">
          <para>Runs the report associated with this screen.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para539977">NEW</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be360">
          <para>Opens screen for creating a new Sales Order.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para539978">VIEW</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be3a8">
          <para>Highlight a Sales Order and then select this button to reach a
          read-only view of the "Edit" screen.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para609999">COPY</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be3f0">
          <para>Highlight a Sales Order and then select this button to create
          a new Sales Order which duplicates the source Sales Order.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para539979">EDIT</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be438">
          <para>Enables you to edit highlighted Sales Order. The edit screen
          is the same as that for creating a new Sales Order--except that when
          editing, the fields will contain Sales Order information.
          Double-clicking on a Sales Order will also bring you to the editing
          screen.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para539980">DELETE</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be480">
          <para>Highlight a Sales Order and then select this button to remove
          the Sales Order from the master list</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

